INSTALL for gedit PerlTidy plugin v1.0
--------------------------------------
copy __init.py__ and the perltidy directory 
to your gedit plugin directory, usually
~/.gnome2/gedit/plugins. Restart gedit.

Edit->Preferences->[Tab]Plugins->PerlTidy
    Options:
        [X] Apply to selection only
            only the selected text (if applicable) is tidied
        [X] Use custom configuration file
            If you have a config file for perltidy that you
            want to include, enter it in the textbox
           
Tools->Run Perltidy
